I'm using a custom array type (in my case ShiftedArrays) and I'm wondering why `sum` is for this array type slow. Even a naive own sum function `f`is faster. Anybody has a clue what's going on?
```julia&gt; using ShiftedArrays, BenchmarkTools
julia&gt; x = randn((1024, 1024, 7, 4));

julia&gt; y = ShiftedArrays.circshift(x, (200, 300, 5, -20));

julia&gt; function f(x)
       r = zero(eltype(x))
       for i in eachindex(x)
           @inbounds r += x[i]
       end
       return r
       end
f (generic function with 1 method)

julia&gt; @btime f($x);
  33.795 ms (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia&gt; @btime f($y);
  70.892 ms (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia&gt; @btime sum($x);
  13.065 ms (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia&gt; @btime sum($y);
  168.689 ms (0 allocations: 0 bytes)```

